            <h1>Net Force</h1>

<div class="page" id="page1">

      <p>
        How quickly an object changes speed, or <a>accelerates</a>, in a given direction depends on the “net”
        force acting on the object in that direction. 
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Net force</b>. The “net” force in a given direction is <i>the sum of all forces acting in that direction</i>
        <u>minus</u> <i>the sum of all forces acting in the opposite direction</i>.  
      </p>
      <p>
        In other words, equal forces on an object that are in opposite directions cancel each other out and do not
        affect the object's motion. Only the "left over" force in that direction will affect the object's acceleration
        in that direction. This "left over" force is the <b>net force</b>.
      </p>



      <p>
     <br/>
      </p><hr/>
